                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d532">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">702.6282/28a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-08-12T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 12, 1942—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3806. According to our Legation at Monrovia, the German Consul is sending code
                    messages to Berlin via Freetown where copies are reported to be taken by the
                    British authorities for the Foreign Office.</p>
                <p>We consider such activities of the German Consul highly dangerous to our
                    interests and are at a loss to understand why these messages should be allowed
                    to pass through British controlled territory. Please endeavor to obtain the
                    cooperation of the appropriate officials in putting a stop to this practice.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
